<TITLE> AL observes Sheikh Mujib's birth anniversary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 17 (bdnews24.com) Awami League central leaders laid floral wreaths at the grave of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman on Monday in observance of his 88th birth anniversary. AL presidium members including Amir Hossain Amu, Abdur Razzak, Tofail Ahmed and Kazi Zafarullah reached the Bangabandhu Memorial Complex in Tungipara around noon to lay wreaths, pay their respects and say prayers. Members of Awami League associate organisations, including Jubo League, Mohila Awami League and Chhatra League, also laid flowers at Sheikh Mujib's graveside. Earlier Monday, Awami League leaders began the day's tributes to mark Bangabandhu's anniversary by laying wreaths at his portrait at Road 32 in Dhanmondi. AL presidium members and acting general secretary Syed Ashraful Islam were among those present on the occasion. While paying respects before Bangabandhu's portrait at Dhanmondi in the morning, Abdur Razzak said to reporters: "We hope the people will be restored their rights and form a people's government through a free and fair election." "We are struggling now to re-establish democracy." Tofail Ahmed expressed hope that measures would soon be taken to bring war criminals and anti-independence elements to justice. bdnews24.com/
